data.text: So if CDC itself is saying that such a large amount of the population has those "underlying medical conditions"... Why has the CDC decided that it has no responsibility for such a large percentage of our population? This is *their* information so they must know it's this high.

Lackawanna County is less than adjacent counties. Wyoming County - which includes Tunkhannock Pennsylvania, CDC says 48.2% of residents have "underlying medical conditions" that put them at higher risk for/with covid. https://t.co/30bkaZihMk
